SABMiller’s Tanzanian Unit Posts 77% Rise in First-Half Net

-- B y   D a v i d   M a l i n g h a   D o y a
-- 
2011-12-05T09:28:12Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-05/sabmiller-s-tanzanian-unit-posts-77-rise-in-first-half-net-1-.html
SABMiller Plc (SAB) ’s Tanzanian unit said
first-half profit jumped 77 percent as sales increased.  Net income surged to 74.7 billion shillings ($45 million)
in the six months through September, from 42.2 billion shillings
a year earlier,  Tanzania Breweries Ltd. (TBL)  said in an e-mailed
statement published in the Dar es Salaam-based Guardian
newspaper today. Sales climbed 32 percent to 386.5 billion
shillings, it said.  The company said it was looking to boost capacity after
“strong” growth in its business over the past year.
“Accordingly, the board has postponed the declaration of an
interim dividend to later this year, pending the outcome of this
review,” it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
